Pour the @water for the rice{300%milliliter}(see pantry for amount) into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%grams} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Halve and peel the @Onion{1}. Chop both into 2cm chunks.

Drain the @King Prawns{225%grams}.

Add the prawns to a #medium bowl{} with the @Cornflour{20%grams} and half the @Chinese Five Spice{1/2%sachet}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw prawns.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Crush the @Salted Peanuts{25%grams} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

Heat the @Oil for Cooking{2%tbsp}(see pantry for amount) in a #large frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, fry the prawns until slightly crispy, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn frequently to ensure it doesn't burn. While the prawns fry, discard any excess cornflour and wipe out the bowl.

When cooked, transfer the prawns to a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{}. Wipe out your pan, then pop back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @Oil{drizzle}(for frying).

Once the oil is hot, add the pepper and onion chunks. Stir-fry until golden and slightly charred, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, in the (now empty) medium bowl, mix together the @Soy Sauce{25%milliliter}, garlic, @Honey{30%grams}, @Sriracha Sauce{15%grams} and remaining @Chinese Five Spice{1/2%sachet} with the @Tomato Ketchup{4%tbsp} and @Water for the Sauce{100%milliliter}(see pantry for both amounts).

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Add the prawns back into the #frying pan{} with the veg and stir in the sticky sauce. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once thickened, remove from the heat. Taste and add more @?salt{}, @?pepper{} and a pinch of @?sugar{} if needed. Add a splash of @?water{} if it's a bit too thick.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then share between your bowls.

Top with the sticky prawns and veg, spooning over the remaining sauce from the pan.

Finish by sprinkling over the peanuts. Enjoy!